{"author": "coding_agent", "parts": [{"text": "The task is complete. Here's a summary of what I did:\n\n1. **Inspected the raw bytes** of both `main.db` and `main.db-wal` using `xxd` before opening with SQLite (critical to avoid WAL corruption).\n\n2. **Identified the encryption**: The WAL file was XOR-encrypted with the byte `0x42`. This was confirmed by XORing the first 4 bytes (`75 3d 44 c0`) which produced `37 7f 06 82` \u2014 the SQLite WAL magic number.\n\n3. **Decrypted the WAL file** by XORing every byte with `0x42` and writing it back in place.\n\n4. **Queried the database** with SQLite, which now properly read the WAL file and returned all 11 records (the base DB had 5 records, and the WAL contained 6 additional ones).\n\n5. **Created `/app/recovered.json`** with all 11 records sorted by id in the requested format."}]}
